                                COLLECTION ACCOUNTS OFTEN REPORTED LONGER THAN FEDERAL LAW ALLOWS
                            </asp:HyperLink>
						</div>
                        <small class="post_meta">By R. David Michaels - Jan 3, 2019</small>
						<p class="card-text blog-description-text">
                            Debt suckers, more commonly known as collection agencies, often improperly report the date a credit 
                            account went delinquent, which results in collection accounts staying on credit reports longer than
                            the law allows.
